  <div class = "large-8 columns">
    <p><b>Parliamentary Champions</b> – We provide opportunities for parliamentarians across the globe to share experiences in tackling malnutrition and discuss ways to accelerate progress. We support parliamentarians keep increase the awareness of nutrition amongst other decision and hold them accountable to their previous commitments. Find out the latest about this initiative here.</p>
        <p> <b>Case Study: Mali</b> – In Mali, ‘The Network of Malian Parliamentarians for the Fight Against Malnutrition’ has been established with the support of Save the Children and World Vision. The network is made up of 13 parliamentarians committed to the fight against malnutrition in Mali. The network has worked closely with the national SUN Civil Society Alliance. The network organized a ‘Day of Exchange’ bringing together 30 parliamentarians to discuss their role in effectively implementing the Multi-Sectoral Action Plan on Nutrition 2014-2018.</p>
  </div>
</div>
